Headlines.Headline: Danaher Buys Nobel Biocare in $2.1 Billion Cash Deal

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Neil MacLucas ZURICH--U.S. healthcare group Danaher Corp. DHR said Monday it will acquire Swiss dental-implant maker Nobel Biocare Holding AG (NOBN.EB) in a cash deal worth about $2.1 billion, to strengthen its position in the dental market. Danaher said it will pay 17.10 Swiss francs ($18.20) a share in a transaction expected to close by late 2014 or early 2015. Headlines.BodyHeadline: Before the Bell: Home Depot, Saks, Centerpoint, Axcan

#text: Stock futures were higher, but the rally attempt appeared fragile with few underlying issues attracting much trade outside of Home Depot

. The home improvement retailer rose over 7 percent on the ECNs after it topped the consensus forecast for its fiscal first quarter by two cents and affirmed its earnings outlook for the year. Currency markets were stable after Monday's wild swings; the euro was kept below $1.17 amid increased expectations for interest rate relief from the European Central Bank in early June. Overnight easing of liquidity by the Bank of Japan and talk of Japan intervention in the currency markets to sell yen on Monday were also contributing to stabilization, some analysts said. The dollar rose to 117.20 yen. Over 2 trillion yen was needed to move the dollar off 115.10, Brussels-based analysts at Fortis Bank said.
